## Slide 3: Introduction
**Background:**
- Competitive job market for engineering graduates
- Traditional interview preparation lacks personalization
- AI technologies offer opportunities for sophisticated solutions

**Problem Statement:**
- Lack of personalized feedback
- Limited access to company-specific questions
- Absence of realistic proctoring environments
- Inadequate skill assessment and roadmap guidance

## Slide 4: Objectives
**Research Objectives:**
1. Design and implement a full-stack web application
2. Integrate AI for personalized question generation
3. Develop realistic proctoring capabilities
4. Create comprehensive career development platform
5. Ensure scalability, reliability, and user experience

## Slide 5: Related Work
**AI in Recruitment:**
- ATS with machine learning for resume screening
- Focus primarily on employer side

**Interview Simulation Systems:**
- Platforms like InterviewBuddy, Pramp
- Limited proctoring and career development features

**Proctoring Technologies:**
- Eye-tracking, facial recognition, browser monitoring
- Designed for academic assessments, not interviews

## Slide 6: Gap Analysis
**Limitations of Existing Solutions:**
- Limited personalization by company/role
- No integrated career development features
- Basic proctoring without behavioral analysis
- Lack of real-time feedback mechanisms

## Slide 7: System Architecture Overview
**Client-Server Architecture:**
- Frontend: Next.js with TypeScript and TailwindCSS
- Backend: Node.js with Express
- AI Integration: Google's Gemini API
- Data Processing: pdf-parse, mammoth

[Visual: System architecture diagram]

## Slide 8: Frontend Architecture
**Key Components:**
- Resume analysis interface
- Skill testing modules
- Career roadmap visualization
- Mock interview interface
- Proctored interview environment

**Technologies:**
- Next.js 14 with App Router
- TypeScript for type safety
- TailwindCSS for responsive design

## Slide 9: Backend Architecture
**Structure:**
- RESTful API endpoints
- Service layers for business logic
- Secure AI service integration
- File processing capabilities

**Technologies:**
- Node.js with Express
- TypeScript for type safety
- pdf-parse and mammoth for file processing

## Slide 10: Data Flow
**Process:**
1. User interacts with frontend UI
2. Frontend makes API calls through proxy
3. Backend processes requests with services
4. AI services invoked server-side
5. Results returned to frontend for visualization

## Slide 11: Resume Analysis Module
**Features:**
- PDF/DOCX resume upload
- Job description comparison
- Job Fit Score (0-100%)
- Detailed improvement suggestions

## Slide 12: Skill Testing System
**Capabilities:**
- Skill identification from resume
- AI-generated challenges:
  - Coding/problem-solving
  - Multiple choice questions
  - Conceptual questions
- Performance evaluation and feedback

## Slide 13: Career Roadmap Feature
**Offerings:**
- Year-wise engineering roadmaps
- Branch-specific guidance
- Progress tracking with checkboxes
- Pro tips for each academic year

## Slide 14: Mock Interview System
**Components:**
- Company-specific question generation
- Role-based difficulty profiling
- Real-time question fetching from Gemini API
- Text-to-speech capabilities
- Live transcription of responses

## Slide 15: Proctored Interview Environment
**Features:**
- Tab-switch detection (Page Visibility API)
- Focus loss monitoring
- Camera/microphone monitoring
- Paste event tracking
- AI-generated content detection

## Slide 16: AI Integration - Real-time Question Generation
**Implementation:**
- Server-side API calls (keys never exposed)
- Retry logic with exponential backoff
- Fallback to cached questions
- Structured JSON responses with validation

## Slide 17: Text-to-Speech (TTS) Implementation
**Functionality:**
- Server-side generation (Google Cloud TTS/ElevenLabs)
- Audio URL generation for playback
- Error handling and fallback mechanisms
- Integration with AI avatar for lip-sync

## Slide 18: Live Transcription
**Technology:**
- Web Speech API implementation
- Real-time interim/final transcripts
- User controls for management
- Browser compatibility handling

## Slide 19: AI Avatar Implementation
**Features:**
- Animated avatar with lip-sync simulation
- Question text display with indicators
- Fallback UI for service unavailability
- Integration with TTS for synchronized speech

## Slide 20: Proctoring - Tab-switch Detection
**Mechanisms:**
- Page Visibility API for state tracking
- Window blur/focus event monitoring
- Configurable strictness levels
- Threshold-based violation flagging

## Slide 21: Camera and Microphone Monitoring
**Capabilities:**
- Automatic permission requests
- Live preview with voice activity detection
- Privacy considerations with consent
- Fallback for denied permissions

## Slide 22: Behavioral Analysis
**Advanced Features:**
- Paste event tracking for cheating detection
- AI-generated content detection
- Suspicious pattern analysis
- Comprehensive reporting mechanisms

## Slide 23: Technical Challenges and Solutions
**API Integration Challenges:**
- Rate limiting and timeout handling
- Server-side key security
- Robust retry mechanisms
- Meaningful fallback experiences

**Solution:** Retry logic with exponential backoff and cached question fallbacks

## Slide 24: Real-time Communication
**Challenges:**
- WebSocket vs. REST API trade-offs
- Latency optimization
- Error handling and recovery

**Solution:** RESTful API endpoints with optimized data structures and client-side caching

## Slide 25: Browser Compatibility
**Challenges:**
- Web Speech API availability
- Media recording capabilities
- CSS rendering differences

**Solution:** Feature detection and graceful degradation with clear user messaging

## Slide 26: Security and Privacy
**Challenges:**
- Secure camera/microphone permissions
- Encryption of sensitive data
- Privacy policy implementation

**Solution:** Strict consent mechanisms, server-side API key management, clear privacy disclosures

